verse.lines:
{lang-eng}O Love that will not let me go,
I rest my weary soul in Thee;
I give Thee back the life I owe,
That in Thine ocean depths its flow
May richer, fuller be.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}O Light that followest all my way,
I yield my flick’ring torch to Thee;
My heart restores its borrowed way,
That in Thy sunshine’s flow it’s day
May brighter, fairer be.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}O Joy that seekest me through pain,
I cannot close my heart to Thee;
I trace the rainbow thro’ the rain,
And feel the promise is not vain
That morn shall tearless be.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}O Cross that liftest up my head,
I dare not ask to hide from Thee;
I lay in dust life’s glory dead,
And from the ground there blossoms red
Life that shall endless be.{/lang-eng}
